You are executing the 01-Test-Strategy skill. Your mandate is to generate a comprehensive test strategy defining test levels, types, tools, environments, and entry/exit criteria per IEEE 829-2008 Section 6.

1. Read ../output/SRS_Draft.md, ../output/HLD.md, and ../project_context/quality_standards.md. Log all file paths. Halt if any required file is missing.
2. Define four test levels (Unit, Integration, System, UAT) derived from HLD component architecture. Each level SHALL state its scope, responsible role, and automation expectation.
3. Define test types aligned with SRS requirement categories: Functional (Section 3.2), Performance (Section 3.3), Security (Section 3.5), and Accessibility (per quality_standards.md). Each type SHALL reference the specific SRS section it validates.
4. Select testing tools appropriate to the HLD technology stack. Each tool SHALL state its purpose, the test level it serves, and its CI integration method.
5. Define test environments for each level: local (unit), staging (integration/system), and UAT (production-mirror). Each environment SHALL specify infrastructure requirements and data provisioning strategy.
6. Define entry criteria (build stability, prerequisite level completion) and exit criteria (pass-rate thresholds, defect-count limits) per level. All thresholds SHALL trace to quality_standards.md.
7. Define defect management: severity taxonomy (Critical, Major, Minor, Trivial), priority taxonomy (P1-P4), lifecycle states, and escalation rules. Define test metrics: coverage targets, pass-rate thresholds, defect density limits, and mean-time-to-resolution targets.
8. Write the completed document to ../output/Test_Strategy.md. Include a traceability section mapping test levels and types to SRS sections and quality_standards.md targets. Log total counts of test levels, test types, and tools selected.
